title: 1-Page taps investors for $35m fresh equity
text:
1-Page was in the market on Monday after a mixed day for Australian shares. Jessica Shapiro by Sarah Thompson Anthony Macdonald 1-Page was seeking to raise $35 million in a non-broker placement after market on Monday, sources told Street Talk Online.
1-Page shares closed at $4.55 on Monday, up 1.1 per cent.
Sources said the placement was likely to be done at a premium to 1-Page's last close and would see investors apply directly to the company for shares, rather than through brokers.
A United States technology investor and a strategic investor are expected to take the bulk of the shares available.
However, it is understood funds investing had been put in contact with the company through Credit Suisse and Canaccord Genuity.
